White House Chief of Staff HowardBaker said President Reagan will address the nation in anationally televised speech Wednesday night at 2100 EST on theTower Commission Report on the arms to Iran scandal.    Baker, in his first news conference as chief of staff, alsosaid that Robert Gates asked that his name be withdrawn fromnomination as director of the Central Intelligence Agency.    Gates said in a letter to the president that it becameapparent it would be a long and difficult process to win Senateconfirmation of the nomination. Reuter&#3;